<DocsLayout title="Implementation" description="Create the backlog in Linear, set up the project with Alembic, and build Coastal Physio with migration-first development.">
  <h1 class="mb-6">Implementation</h1>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">You know the loop. The new dimensions: three types of work (application tickets, infrastructure tickets, migration tickets), a new project management tool (Linear), and migration-first development — every database change starts with an Alembic migration, not application code.</p>

  <Callout variant="info">
    <p class="text-sm"><strong>This project uses Linear for project management.</strong> Same kanban workflow as GitHub Projects — backlog, in progress, done. Different interface, different features. We switch tools deliberately to demonstrate that the project management skill transfers. If you can manage a backlog in GitHub Projects, you can manage it in Linear.</p>
  </Callout>

  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-8">Work through these in order:</p>

